<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
This varietal name has been treated as unavailable under Art. 45.6 ICZN by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 367" publicationUrl="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" refId="B14" refString="Breure, ASH, Ablett, JD, 2014. Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London. ZooKeys 392: 1 - 367, DOI: 10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" title="Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London." url="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" volume="392" year="2014">Breure and Ablett (2014</bibRefCitation>
: 96). Paul Callomon (pers. commun.) has suggested that this should be reconsidered and doubted if a lectotype of the nominal name already existed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Our opinion is as follows:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
Preston undoubtedly had a series of specimens at hand when describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="interruptus" subGenus="Drymaeus">Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus</taxonomicName>
; both the wording &quot;to be greatly variable&quot; and &quot;its principle forms&quot; are indicative of this.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979</bibRefCitation>
: 120) mentioned this taxon in his listing under 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drymaeus (Mesembrinus)" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesembrinus">Drymaeus (Mesembrinus)</taxonomicName>
Albers, 1850, and stated &quot;HT BMNH 1914.4.3.38&quot; [referring to a single specimen, thus qualifying Art. 74.6.1.2 jo. 74.3]; Art. 74.6 ICZN rules this statement as a lectotype designation. It should be noted, however, that Breure did not list the &quot;var. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; of Preston in his paper (cf. point d below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<normalizedToken originalValue="KÃ¶hler">Koehler</normalizedToken>
(1997) also concluded that this taxon was described from several specimens but said &quot;A holotype has not been designated. Therefore, the present specimen [ZMB 59597] is a syntype. Consequently, the specimen in the BMNH referred to as holotype by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979)</bibRefCitation>
is a syntype&quot;. Overlooking, as explained in the previous item, the lectotype designation under Art. 74.6 (see previous point).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
Reconsidering the (un)availability under Art. 45.6, it is important to note that var. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed before 1961 and has to be treated as subspecific (see the contributions of Steve Lingafelter and Doug Yanega on the Taxacom listing, http://to.ly/zFZO). It may be noted that the only reference to this taxon after 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Prestonâs">Preston's</normalizedToken>
publication is in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, HB" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 49" refId="B5" refString="Baker, HB, 1926. The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV. Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan 167: 1 - 49" title="The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV." volume="167" year="1926">Baker (1926</bibRefCitation>
: 44), who regarded it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="L.Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1848" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus granadensis" order="Pulmonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Bulimus granadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pfeiffer, 1848 (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Richardson, CL" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B114" refString="Richardson, CL, 1995. Bulimulidae: catalog of species. Tryonia 28" title="Bulimulidae: catalog of species." volume="28" year="1995">Richardson 1995</bibRefCitation>
: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
While 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus subsp. var. var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" subGenus="Drymaeus" subSpecies="var." variety="pallidus">Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus var. pallidus</taxonomicName>
is an available name, we concur with 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, HB" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 49" refId="B5" refString="Baker, HB, 1926. The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV. Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan 167: 1 - 49" title="The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV." volume="167" year="1926">Baker (1926)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Richardson, CL" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B114" refString="Richardson, CL, 1995. Bulimulidae: catalog of species. Tryonia 28" title="Bulimulidae: catalog of species." volume="28" year="1995">Richardson (1995)</bibRefCitation>
to consider this taxon as a synonym of the nominal form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
The specimen of var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the NHMUK is now designated lectotype (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">design. n.</emphasis>
) to fixate this synonymisation. The text in 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 367" publicationUrl="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" refId="B14" refString="Breure, ASH, Ablett, JD, 2014. Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London. ZooKeys 392: 1 - 367, DOI: 10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" title="Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London." url="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" volume="392" year="2014">Breure and Ablett (2014</bibRefCitation>
: 96), under 'Type 
<normalizedToken originalValue="materialâ">material'</normalizedToken>
, should be corrected as follows: &quot;NHMUK 1914.3.38, lectotype; 1914.4.3.39-40, 42-43, four paralectotypes&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
